# DOCX Generator Reference

## Prerequisites

Before generating the resume document:
1. Read `/mnt/skills/public/docx/SKILL.md` for docx-js rules and validation steps
2. Ensure `docx` npm package is installed: `npm install -g docx`
3. All sections must be reviewed and confirmed by the user before generation

## Architecture

The resume is generated as a single .docx file using the `docx` npm package (docx-js), then converted to PDF using LibreOffice for dual-format output.

## Template Code

Below is the complete, production-ready template. Adapt it based on which sections the user needs.

```javascript
const fs = require('fs');
const { Document, Packer, Paragraph, TextRun, AlignmentType, BorderStyle,
        LevelFormat, TabStopType, ExternalHyperlink } = require('docx');

// Content width calculation: page width - left margin - right margin
// US Letter: 12240 - 720 - 720 = 10800 DXA
// A4: 11906 - 720 - 720 = 10466 DXA
const CONTENT_WIDTH = 10800; // Adjust for A4 if needed

// ===== HELPER FUNCTIONS =====

// Section heading with bottom border
function sectionHeading(text) {
  return new Paragraph({
    spacing: { before: 200, after: 60 },
    border: { bottom: { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 6, color: "000000", space: 1 } },
    children: [
      new TextRun({ text: text.toUpperCase(), bold: true, font: "Arial", size: 22 })
    ]
  });
}

// Bullet point with configurable spacing
function bullet(textRuns, spacing = { before: 30, after: 30 }) {
  return new Paragraph({
    numbering: { reference: "bullets", level: 0 },
    spacing: spacing,
    children: textRuns
  });
}

// Two-column line with right-aligned second column (for dates/locations)
function twoColLine(leftText, rightText, leftBold = false, rightBold = false, size = 20, spacing = { before: 0, after: 0 }) {
  return new Paragraph({
    tabStops: [{ type: TabStopType.RIGHT, position: CONTENT_WIDTH }],
    spacing: spacing,
    children: [
      new TextRun({ text: leftText, bold: leftBold, font: "Arial", size: size }),
      new TextRun({ text: "\t" }),
      new TextRun({ text: rightText, bold: rightBold, font: "Arial", size: size })
    ]
  });
}

// Spacer paragraph
function spacer(before = 80) {
  return new Paragraph({ spacing: { before: before, after: 0 }, children: [] });
}

// ===== LINK HELPERS =====

// Create a clickable hyperlink inline
function link(url, displayText, size = 20, bold = false) {
  return new ExternalHyperlink({
    link: url,
    children: [new TextRun({
      text: displayText, font: "Arial", size: size,
      color: "0563C1", underline: {}, bold: bold
    })]
  });
}

// Plain text run
function text(content, bold = false, size = 20) {
  return new TextRun({ text: content, bold: bold, font: "Arial", size: size });
}

// ===== DOCUMENT STRUCTURE =====

const doc = new Document({
  numbering: {
    config: [{
      reference: "bullets",
      levels: [{
        level: 0,
        format: LevelFormat.BULLET,
        text: "\u2022",
        alignment: AlignmentType.LEFT,
        style: { paragraph: { indent: { left: 360, hanging: 360 } } }
      }]
    }]
  },
  styles: {
    default: {
      document: { run: { font: "Arial", size: 20 } }
    }
  },
  sections: [{
    properties: {
      page: {
        size: { width: 12240, height: 15840 }, // US Letter
        margin: { top: 540, right: 720, bottom: 540, left: 720 }
      }
    },
    children: [
      // ===== NAME & CONTACT =====
      // Name and title: same size, both bold
      new Paragraph({
        alignment: AlignmentType.CENTER,
        spacing: { after: 30 },
        children: [
          text("First Last", true, 32),
          text("  -  Target Role Title", true, 32)
        ]
      }),
      // Contact line with clickable links
      new Paragraph({
        alignment: AlignmentType.CENTER,
        spacing: { after: 80 },
        children: [
          text("City, Country  |  ", false, 18),
          link("mailto:email@example.com", "email@example.com", 18),
          text("  |  +1 234 567 8900  |  ", false, 18),
          link("https://linkedin.com/in/username", "linkedin.com/in/username", 18),
          // Add GitHub if relevant:
          // text("  |  ", false, 18),
          // link("https://github.com/username", "github.com/username", 18),
        ]
      }),

      // ===== PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY =====
      sectionHeading("Professional Summary"),
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { before: 60, after: 0 },
        children: [
          // Mix bold and regular text for key metrics
          text("Role with "),
          text("X years", true),
          text(" of experience doing [core competency]. [Achievement with "),
          text("bold metrics", true),
          text("]. [Second achievement]. [Credibility signal]. Hands-on with X, Y, Z.")
        ]
      }),

      // ===== SKILLS =====
      sectionHeading("Skills"),
      bullet([
        text("Technical: ", true),
        text("Tool1, Tool2, Tool3, Framework1, Framework2")
      ], { before: 40, after: 20 }),
      bullet([
        text("Product: ", true),
        text("Skill1, Skill2, Skill3, Methodology1")
      ], { before: 20, after: 20 }),
      // Optional third line for ATS coverage:
      // bullet([
      //   text("Also worked with: ", true),
      //   text("Tool4, Tool5, Concept1, Concept2")
      // ], { before: 20, after: 20 }),

      // ===== EXPERIENCE =====
      sectionHeading("Experience"),

      // --- Company 1 (Current) ---
      twoColLine("Company Name", "Location", true, false, 22, { before: 60, after: 0 }),
      twoColLine("Current Title", "Start Date - Present", false, false, 20, { before: 20, after: 0 }),
      // Optional promotion line:
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { before: 20, after: 40 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({
            text: "Promoted: Previous Title \u2192 Current Title",
            italics: true, font: "Arial", size: 19
          })
        ]
      }),

      // Bullets with bold metrics and clickable links
      bullet([
        text("Built "),
        link("https://product-url.com", "Product Name", 20, true),
        text(", description of what it does. Achieved "),
        text("key metric", true),
        text(".")
      ]),

      bullet([
        text("Second achievement with "),
        text("another bold metric", true),
        text(" and context.")
      ]),

      // --- Company 2 (Previous) ---
      spacer(100),
      twoColLine("Previous Company", "Location", true, false, 21, { before: 0, after: 0 }),
      twoColLine("Title", "Start Date - End Date", false, false, 20, { before: 20, after: 20 }),

      bullet([text("Achievement bullet.")]),

      // ===== PROJECTS (Optional) =====
      // sectionHeading("Projects"),
      // twoColLine("Project Name", "Date Range", true, false, 21, { before: 60, after: 0 }),
      // bullet([
      //   text("Description. "),
      //   link("https://github.com/user/repo", "GitHub", 20),
      //   text(". Tech stack: X, Y, Z. "),
      //   text("Key metric", true),
      //   text(".")
      // ]),

      // ===== EDUCATION =====
      sectionHeading("Education"),
      twoColLine("UNIVERSITY NAME", "Location", true, false, 21, { before: 60, after: 0 }),
      twoColLine("Degree, Specialization - GPA", "Year Range", false, false, 20, { before: 20, after: 20 }),

      // School marks (India, early career only):
      // spacer(60),
      // twoColLine("SCHOOL NAME", "Location", true, false, 21, { before: 0, after: 0 }),
      // twoColLine("Class XII, Board - Percentage", "Year", false, false, 20, { before: 20, after: 0 }),
      // twoColLine("Class X, Board - Percentage", "Year", false, false, 20, { before: 20, after: 0 }),

      // ===== CERTIFICATIONS (Optional) =====
      // sectionHeading("Certifications"),
      // bullet([text("Certification Name - Issuing Body (Year)")]),
    ]
  }]
});

// ===== OUTPUT =====
Packer.toBuffer(doc).then(buffer => {
  fs.writeFileSync("/home/claude/Resume_Output.docx", buffer);
  console.log("Resume created successfully!");
});
```

## Post-Generation Steps

### 1. Validate
```bash
python /mnt/skills/public/docx/scripts/office/validate.py Resume_Output.docx
```

### 2. Convert to PDF
```bash
python /mnt/skills/public/docx/scripts/office/soffice.py --headless --convert-to pdf Resume_Output.docx --outdir /home/claude/
```

### 3. Preview
```bash
pdftoppm -jpeg -r 150 Resume_Output.pdf preview
```
Then use the `view` tool to check the rendered output.

### 4. Page Count Check
```bash
ls preview*.jpg
```
If the resume spills to two pages, first try to fit on one page:
- Reduce top/bottom margins (minimum 540 DXA = 0.375 inches)
- Reduce spacing between sections
- Reduce bullet spacing to { before: 20, after: 20 }
- As a last resort, reduce body font to size: 19 (9.5pt)
- NEVER go below 9pt body text

If after all tightening it still doesn't fit AND the content is genuinely strong (not filler), allow two pages. The test: does every line on page two make the hiring manager more interested? If yes, keep it. If no, cut until it fits on one page.

For two-page resumes, ensure page breaks fall at natural section boundaries (not mid-bullet). The strongest content must be on page one.

### 5. Deliver
Copy both .docx and .pdf to `/mnt/user-data/outputs/` and use `present_files` to share with the user.

## Formatting Cheatsheet

| Element | Font | Size (half-points) | Bold |
|---------|------|-------------------|------|
| Name + Title | Arial | 32 (16pt) | Yes |
| Contact info | Arial | 18 (9pt) | No |
| Section headings | Arial | 22 (11pt) | Yes, uppercase |
| Company name | Arial | 22 (11pt) | Yes |
| Job title + dates | Arial | 20 (10pt) | No |
| Promotion line | Arial | 19 (9.5pt) | No, italic |
| Body text / bullets | Arial | 20 (10pt) | No (except metrics) |
| Skills category labels | Arial | 20 (10pt) | Yes |

## Critical Rules

- NEVER use `\n` in text runs. Use separate Paragraph elements.
- NEVER use unicode bullets (`\u2022` as text). Use LevelFormat.BULLET numbering.
- ALWAYS set explicit page size (docx-js defaults to A4).
- ALWAYS validate after generation.
- ALWAYS preview the PDF conversion before delivering.
- ALWAYS use DXA units for widths, never percentages.
- ALWAYS make tab stop position match content width for right-alignment.
- ExternalHyperlink requires the full URL including protocol (https://).
- For mailto links, use "mailto:email@example.com" as the link.
